Q5.

   - justify-items sets the horizontal alignment of all items in the grid/container.

   - justify-self sets the horizontal alignment of a single specific item.


EXAMPLE:- 

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>justify-items vs justify-self</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      background: #f0f0f0;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .container {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 100px);
      grid-template-rows: 100px;
      gap: 10px;
      border: 2px solid #000;
      background: white;
      padding: 10px;
      justify-items: center; /* Affects all items */
    }

    .box {
      background-color: peachpuff;
      padding: 10px;
      font-weight: bold;
      border-radius: 5px;
    }

    .custom {
      justify-self: end; /* Overrides container's justify-items for this one box */
      background-color: lightcoral;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="box">1</div>
    <div class="box custom">2</div>
    <div class="box">3</div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
